addressee: Nevaeh the dog across the street
word_meaning: Hard to say. She had her own words for things from the start but it's difficult to say when she began to use the actual word \"dog\". The first time that I can recall noticing was when Nevaeh was barking which used to frighten her and she just nonchalantly reported what she was noticing. \"Dog\" she said as if it was nothing. And... I didn't really think of making anything of it myself as it was just another word in her vocabulary -- that happened to coincide in this case with English.
notes: Again she has always had a language of her own consistent sounds and gestures. Learning English and using it to replace her own system has been a fairly gradual transitional process such that it's rare that any individual milestone really sticks out.
